# Research & Validation Bias

Good in-sample metrics are not evidence until validated without reuse of the test slice.

## Rules

- **One hypothesis, one primary test** — Log in `02_research/hypothesis_log.md` before heavy iteration. Note how many variants were tried.
- **Holdout** — Reserve a final OOS period (or paper-trading window) never used for tuning, feature selection, or kill/keep decisions until the end.
- **S1 equities panel artifacts** — `s1_factor_panel.ipynb` writes two parquets controlled by `RESEARCH_IS_FRACTION` (default `0.70`):
  - `s1_factor_panel_train.parquet` — chronological train / research IS (first fraction of unique trading dates). Use this for factor IC / Alphalens screens. Do **not** re-split it.
  - `s1_factor_panel_full.parquet` — full sample (census). Reserved for later model OOS / backtests; do **not** use it to pick windows or freeze `feature_spec`.
- **Walk-forward** — Retrain and re-tune on rolling train windows; measure on the subsequent out-of-sample window.
- **Purged / embargoed CV** — When labels overlap in time (e.g. 5-day forward return), purge training rows whose label window overlaps test, and add an embargo gap.
- **No peeking at OOS** — If OOS degrades, do not tweak and re-test on the same OOS; fix on train/validation only or wait for new data.
- **Report friction** — Net of fees, spread, slippage, and realistic position limits. Flag results that flip sign after costs.
- **Forward test parity** — Paper/live code must use the same signal timing, universe rules, and lag logic as the backtest.

## Metric discipline

- Prefer deflated Sharpe, PBO, or simple "variants tried vs. best" accounting when running many experiments.
- Compare against a naive baseline (buy-and-hold, random timing, zero signal) on the same universe and costs.

## Red flags

Single global `GridSearchCV` on all history, test set reused across notebook reruns, "we dropped 2020" without PIT reason, Sharpe > 3 with no OOS, re-fetching full history for factor IC when the train parquet already exists, screening windows on `s1_factor_panel_full.parquet`.
